[For a discussion of carbapenemases, see moderator ML's comments in prior ProMED-mail post: Enterobacteriaceae, carbapenem resistant - Europe: survey 20130712.1822582.

Kuching, with a population of 325 132 in the north western part of the island of Borneo, is the capital and the most populous city in the state of Sarawak, Malaysia (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuching). Sibu Hospital is the 2nd largest hospital in the state of Sarawak; it is the main tertiary and referral hospital for the Central Region of Sarawak (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sibu_Hospital). - Mod.ML

